ogical result of the major governmental changes which have taken place since Stalin's death.\n\nthere may be further ministerial reorganizations in the Soviet Government requiring constitutional amendments beyond those ratified by the Supreme Soviet on 15 March.\n\nThe existing state of confusion within the Soviet Government may thus be prolonged for a considerable period. Such a state of flux might preclude the Kremlin's embarking on an adventurous foreign policy and would provide strong motivation for a continuation of the current \"peace offensive", "token_count": 90, "token_end_0based": 89, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "comment the confusion among lower-level administrators is a logical result of the major governmental changes which have taken place since stalin's death there may be further ministerial reorganizations in the soviet government requiring constitutional amendments beyond those ratified by the supreme soviet on 15 march the existing state of confusion within the soviet government may thus be prolonged for a considerable period such a state of flux might preclude the kremlin's embarking on an adventurous foreign policy and would provide strong motivation for a continuation of the current peace offensive", "unred_source_page": 4}
